{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018ok9uEjzG7e5iq8BtJwkhN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The headless service has no endpoints yet because `es-0` is not ready. The endpoints are only populated when pods are ready. So `es-nodes` doesn't resolve to any IPs.\n\nThe fix is to use individual pod DNS names (`es-0.es-nodes`, `es-1.es-nodes`, `es-2.es-nodes`) which are created by Kubernetes for StatefulSet pods using the `hostname.subdomain` pattern, regardless of readiness.\n\nActually wait - for headless services with StatefulSets, Kubernetes creates DNS entries for each pod even before the pod is ready. These are created based on the StatefulSet pod names and the serviceName field. So `es-0.es-nodes.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` should resolve as soon as the pod exists (not just when it's ready).\nI need to update the ConfigMap with the specific pod DNS names and then restart the pods so they pick up the new configuration. Since the elasticsearch.yml is read at startup, I'll update the ConfigMap and delete the es-0 pod to force a restart, though I should consider the cluster formation requirements with all three nodes. The `cluster.initial_master_nodes` setting requires all listed nodes to be present simultaneously for the initial bootstrap, which conflicts with StatefulSet's sequential pod creation. Once the cluster forms, this setting is ignored, but the catch is that with three nodes specified, we can't bootstrap with just one or two pods running.\n\nI can solve this two ways: either use `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` to spin up all three pods at once, or bootstrap with just `es-0` in the initial_master_nodes setting and let the other nodes join afterward through discovery. The parallel approach is cleaner and more straightforward, so I'll go with that—all three pods will start together and can form the cluster immediately.\n\nI also need to fix the DNS discovery so the nodes can actually find each other. I'll explicitly list all three pod DNS names in the `discovery.seed_hosts` configuration so they can communicate regardless of readiness status. Then I'll delete the current StatefulSet and reapply the updated manifest with these changes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1669,"cache_read_input_tokens":39651,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1669},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"279f27af-7143-4116-9f52-e911a9a445e0","uuid":"13805787-6e89-4890-9271-07a9078e5272","request_id":"req_011Cc6kKMWXWoQVmyomeS6fo"}
