{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017v3Yq1qPuJPhMfc6hVnx38","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The DNS configuration looks correct. The search domains include `elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` and `svc.cluster.local`. So `es-1.es-nodes` should resolve to `es-1.es-nodes.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`.\n\nBut let me check if the headless service for StatefulSets creates DNS entries for non-ready pods. In Kubernetes, the behavior depends on whether `publishNotReadyAddresses` is set on the service.\n\nFor StatefulSets, the headless service typically needs to have `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` to include pods that are not yet ready. Without this, only ready pods are included in the DNS, and since the pods are not ready (they haven't formed the cluster yet), the DNS lookup fails.\nThis is the classic bootstrap problem—the pods need to discover each other to form the cluster, but DNS won't list them until they're ready. Setting `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service solves this by making Kubernetes publish DNS entries for all matching pods regardless of readiness state.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":169,"cache_read_input_tokens":50411,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":169},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"279f27af-7143-4116-9f52-e911a9a445e0","uuid":"8d34e03a-8cdb-4267-9167-e3aa68fcb7f6","request_id":"req_011Cc6koaVQUP7QhVqnA8HnR"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017v3Yq1qPuJPhMfc6hVnx38","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found the issue — the headless service needs `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`. Without it, Kubernetes only adds DNS entries for **ready** pods, but ES pods can't become ready until the cluster forms (classic chicken-and-egg). Let me patch the service."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":169,"cache_read_input_tokens":50411,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":169},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"279f27af-7143-4116-9f52-e911a9a445e0","uuid":"5e371c67-9793-4054-8410-245758f00662","request_id":"req_011Cc6koaVQUP7QhVqnA8HnR"}
