{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FK4H9t5TVwhB9y8ATU2uys","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reads and writes succeed. Here's a summary of what was deployed:\n\n**Resources created:**\n- `ConfigMap/es-config` — `elasticsearch.yml` with xpack security + TLS (HTTP and transport) using the existing `es-http-tls` secret\n- `Service/es-nodes` (headless, `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`) — used for cluster formation/discovery on port 9300\n- `Service/es-http` — ClusterIP service on port 9200 for HTTPS access\n- `PodDisruptionBudget/es-pdb` — `minAvailable: 2`\n- `StatefulSet/es` — 3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`, mounting TLS certs and `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` from the existing secrets\n\n**Two non-obvious issues resolved during deployment:**\n1. `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` — required so all 3 pods start simultaneously; sequential startup deadlocks because `cluster.initial_master_nodes` needs quorum before any node becomes ready\n2. `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service — required so Kubernetes publishes DNS endpoints for non-ready pods; without it, nodes can't resolve each other's hostnames, which blocks cluster formation\n\n**Verification:** cluster is green (3/3 nodes), HTTPS reachable at `es-http:9200`, write + read confirmed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":593,"cache_read_input_tokens":54510,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":593},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"279f27af-7143-4116-9f52-e911a9a445e0","uuid":"a4160127-6bc2-49e2-a2d0-18a69f6d7431","request_id":"req_011Cc6kx4fHm9Twb32GFjqeF"}
